export default function audioPlayer(trackName,command) {
    const trackList = {
        monologue1: 'https://storage.googleapis.com/secondbodyuploads/Sublet.mp3',
        monologue2: 'https://storage.googleapis.com/secondbodyuploads/Zombies.mp3',
        monologue3: 'https://storage.googleapis.com/secondbodyuploads/AudioEngineer.mp3',
        monologue4: '',
        monologue5: '',
        monologue6: '',

        dialogue1: 'https://storage.googleapis.com/secondbodyuploads/S_2Weeks.mp3',
        dialogue1B: 'https://storage.googleapis.com/secondbodyuploads/M_2Weeks.mp3',
        dialogue2: 'https://storage.googleapis.com/secondbodyuploads/Multipost_Discovery--Rep.mp3"',
        dialogue2B: 'https://storage.googleapis.com/secondbodyuploads/Multipost_Discovery--Prospect.mp3',
        dialogue3: 'https://storage.googleapis.com/secondbodyuploads/MultiPost_competitors--rep.mp3',
        dialogue3B: 'https://storage.googleapis.com/secondbodyuploads/MultiPost_competitors--prospect.mp3',
        dialogue4: '',
        dialogue4B: '',
        dialogue5: '',
        dialogue5B: '',
        dialogue6: '',
        dialogue6B: '',
    }
    if (typeof(window.audio)!='undefined' && !window.audio) {window.audio = new Audio();}
    audio.src = trackList[trackName]
    console.log (`going to ${command} ${trackName}`);
    audio[command]();

    

}
